  "prompt": "Who is Nira Radia and what did she actually do?",
  "response": "Niira Radia is an Indian corporate lobbyist who became widely known due to her involvement in a major scandal called the Radia tapes controversy. She is the founder of Vaishnavi Corporate Communications and known for her connections with high-profile businesses and politicians.\n\nThe Radia tapes controversy emerged in 2010 when recordings of phone conversations between Radia and various politicians, businessmen, and journalists were leaked to the public. These tapes revealed attempts to influence political decisions and policy-making, leading to accusations of corruption and favoritism. The scandal highlighted the deep connections between corporate interests and political power in India.\n\nRadia was investigated for her role in these activities, though she claimed that her lobbying efforts were legitimate and within the bounds of the law. The controversy raised significant questions about the role of lobbyists in Indian politics and business, and led to calls for greater transparency and regulation in these fields.",
